mrigger added on 2019-08-09 23:00:43:
Consider the test case below:
CREATE TABLE t0(c0);
INSERT INTO t0(c0) VALUES (0);
CREATE INDEX i0 ON t0(NULL > c0) WHERE (NULL NOT NULL);
SELECT * FROM t0 WHERE ((NULL IS FALSE) IS FALSE); -- expected: row is fetched: actual: row is not fetched
I would expect the row in the table being fetched. However, it is only fetched if the index is not created.
